                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          It's been a while since we connected with you in the last blog. We hope it provided you with some clarity on how you can choose a career for yourself. This time, let's take an example closer to home. Amitabh Bachchan, one of the most renowned veteran actors in the Bollywood industry, faced several rejections in the initial phase of his career. People mocked him for his height only to view him with reverence and respect later. What's noteworthy here is that people who follow their passion carve a career out of it and do not give up. On that note, we have lined up more valuable tips for you to decide on a career. These include: tallying the job's requirements with your needs, job to course approach, reflecting to gain clarity, analysing your personality traits, visualising your future, thinking of the long run, and giving time and patience. 

                        </p>

                       
