                            </div>
<br><br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">1. <u>Tally the job's requirements with your needs:
                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          To get a more realistic perspective on the career path or job you seek, it is imperative to compare your needs and expectations with their requirements. Preferably, your needs and expectations should overlap with the job's requirements. For instance, if you are an aspiring pilot who wishes to work for an esteemed airline, you need to know that this job requires frequent travelling. If frequent travelling and longer working hours are not your cups of tea, you would have to reconsider your job options. 

                            
                        
                        </p>

                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">2.<u> Job to course approach:
                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          Most people often progress from short term to long term goals. They first choose a course they wish to pursue and then proceed to search for the job opportunities available under the scope of that course. Instead, it is advisable that you progress from long term to short term goals. Try gaining clarity on what profession you want to pursue, and then opt for courses that would provide you with the required qualifications to pursue your dream job. 

                        </p>

                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2F5293.jpg?alt=media&token=4d6d0a69-b3a1-45ab-b9bc-76985bd2345a" >
                            </div>
                            </div>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">3.<u> Reflect to gain clarity:

                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          Inability to decide on one particular job option and fluctuating between multiple options every now and then is a common concern among many students. To address this concern, we suggest you reflect on the factors mentioned below:
<br>
                          1. <b>Skill set :</b> Ascertain whether you possess the required skills to pursue the career options you are considering. Let's take an example, if you aim to become a fashion designer, consider whether you know the basics of stitching, sketching, and creating aesthetic outfit designs.
                          <br>
                          2. <b>Knowledge :</b> Examine whether you possess a basic knowledge of the field. An aspiring fashion designer should have some basic knowledge about silhouettes, cloth materials, aesthetic and appealing designs, complementing colour palettes, and the latest trends in the fashion market. 
                            <br>
                          3. <b>Resources :</b> Check if you have ample financial resources to pursue the job of your choice. For instance, ascertain if you have enough financial resources to undertake preparation classes for a NIFT (National Institute of Fashion Technology) entrance exam and pay for a course in this institution. You can also check for scholarship opportunities offered in such esteemed institutes.
                          <br>
                          4. <b>Passion :</b> Reflect on how passionate and dedicated you are to pursuing a particular job and learning about the same. You should be passionately interested in learning about fashion and exploring new ideas in this domain to become a successful fashion designer.
                          
                        </p>

                        <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">4.<u> Analyse your personality traits:
                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          Every job requires a set of soft skills or personality factors best suited for the profession. It is crucial to assess your personality traits and emotional intelligence to verify whether you are fit for the job. For instance, if you aspire to become a psychologist, you need to possess interpersonal skills, communication skills, empathy and a substantial level of emotional intelligence and stability to pursue this profession. 

                        </p>
                        

                        <div class="row" >
                          <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                              <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2F6887196.jpg?alt=media&token=d909a4a4-a0ea-4256-bf9c-88dd617c8e1c" >
                          </div>
                          </div>
                      <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">5.<u> Visualise and conceptualise your future:


                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          Most people create a vision board to keep themselves motivated and focused on who they want to become. You can create a vision board for yourself by pasting quotes, articles, pictures, slogans or any material that inspires you to pursue your dream job. This board would be a great tool in helping you visualise your future and act as a reminder of who you want to be in the future. You can also create a vision diary where you put all your desired articles and materials and glance through them regularly. 
    
                        </p>
                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2F5899209.jpg?alt=media&token=946533f6-edd8-4beb-8188-b36782471697" >
                            </div>
                            </div>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">6.<u> Think of the long run: 


                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          Deciding a suitable career for yourself is a choice that will impact your life in the long run. Keeping this in mind, when you choose a career path, remember that you will have to pursue this path for the next forty to fifty years. Although there are cases where people switch their professions and change their fields during their careers, this process takes time and has its own challenges. Therefore, it is advisable to make an informed and well-contemplated decision right from the beginning.
    
                        </p>

  <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">7.<u> Give time and practice patience: 
                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                          Most importantly, figuring out a career for yourself is a process that will take some time. You may not be able to choose overnight; however, conducting research and paying close attention to your interests, needs, skills, and qualities will lead you to figure out what you want to do. It is pivotal to stay patient and trust this process. Taking a crucial decision about your career may take time, and the process may be a bit long, but it's worth the wait and effort!
                        </p>
                       
